    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my realtor just mentioned something about needing an escrow account for this house i'm looking at in toronto. i've never bought a place before so i'm kinda lost. can u explain what escrow actually is and why it's even used in the closing process?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Escrow, in a real estate context, is like a secure, neutral holding tank for your money and documents during the transaction. A neutral third party, the escrow agent, holds the earnest money and the final funds until all the conditions of the sale are met. It's used to ensure that both the buyer and the seller fulfill their obligations, protecting both parties until the deal is officially closed.",
      "source": "target",
