    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense. so it's basically just a way to make sure nobody gets ripped off while the paperwork is being processed? i'm a bit nervous about just handing over a bunch of cash to a middleman. what exactly are they looking out for during that time?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You've got the core idea right; escrow is a protection mechanism against being ripped off. The escrow agent is essentially a fiduciary, meaning they have a legal duty to act in the best interest of both the buyer and the seller. They are looking out for the agreed-upon terms, making sure the title is clear, that inspections are completed, and that all contractual deadlines are met before releasing any funds.",
      "source": "target",
