    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "okay i get the fiduciary part. but it still feels weird having this third party just sitting on the money like it's some kind of vault. is there anything else they handle besides just the cash? like what happens if something goes wrong with the house right at the end?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Beyond just holding the cash, the escrow agent manages the entire administrative flow, which can involve coordinating title searches, insurance requirements, and verifying legal documents. If something goes wrong right at the end—like a major inspection failure or a title issue—the escrow agreement provides a clear pathway for resolving it, often allowing for renegotiation or, if necessary, a safe termination of the contract without losing your earnest money. This provides a structured way to deal with complications.",
      "source": "target",
